HEADWORD: Dowser
<hw>Dows"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A divining
rod used in searching for water, ore, etc., a dowsing rod.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who uses the dowser or divining rod.</def>
<rj><au>Eng. Cyc.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dowst</ent>⟦br⟧
